  <!-- TEST PLAN PANEL -->
  <section id="testplan-section" class="doc-section">
    <h2>üìã Test Plan</h2>
    
    <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
    <h4>1.1 Purpose</h4>
    <p>This Test Plan describes the testing approach, scope, resources, and schedule for the E-Commerce Platform Release v2.5. The objective is to ensure quality, reliability, and user satisfaction before production deployment.</p>
    
    <h4>1.2 Scope</h4>
    <p><strong>In Scope:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>User authentication and authorization (login, logout, password reset)</li>
      <li>Shopping cart and checkout flow</li>
      <li>Form validation and error handling</li>
      <li>Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 Level AA)</li>
      <li>Security testing (XSS, CSRF, SQL injection)</li>
      <li>Performance benchmarks (page load, LCP, memory)</li>
      <li>Cross-browser compatibility (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)</li>
      <li>Mobile responsive design</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Out of Scope:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Third-party payment gateway internal logic</li>
      <li>Legacy admin panel (planned for v3.0)</li>
      <li>Email server infrastructure</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. Test Strategy</h3>
    <h4>2.1 Testing Levels</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Unit Testing:</strong> Developers ensure 80%+ code coverage</li>
      <li><strong>Integration Testing:</strong> API contracts, database transactions</li>
      <li><strong>System Testing:</strong> End-to-end user workflows</li>
      <li><strong>Acceptance Testing:</strong> UAT with stakeholders</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>2.2 Testing Types</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Functional:</strong> Core features and business logic</li>
      <li><strong>Non-Functional:</strong> Performance, security, accessibility</li>
      <li><strong>Regression:</strong> Ensure existing features remain intact</li>
      <li><strong>Smoke:</strong> Quick sanity checks post-deployment</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Test Environment</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Environment</th><th>Purpose</th><th>URL</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Development</td><td>Dev testing</td><td>dev.example.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Staging</td><td>Pre-prod validation</td><td>staging.example.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Production</td><td>Live environment</td><td>example.com</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>4. Test Deliverables</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Test Cases (23 total)</li>
      <li>Requirements Traceability Matrix (RTM)</li>
      <li>Bug Reports (28 identified)</li>
      <li>Test Execution Summary</li>
      <li>Final Test Report</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. Schedule</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Phase</th><th>Duration</th><th>Start Date</th><th>End Date</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Test Planning</td><td>3 days</td><td>Oct 1</td><td>Oct 3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Test Design</td><td>5 days</td><td>Oct 4</td><td>Oct 8</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Test Execution</td><td>10 days</td><td>Oct 9</td><td>Oct 18</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Bug Fixing</td><td>7 days</td><td>Oct 19</td><td>Oct 25</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Regression Testing</td><td>3 days</td><td>Oct 26</td><td>Oct 28</td></tr>
        <tr><td>UAT</td><td>2 days</td><td>Oct 29</td><td>Oct 30</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>6. Resources</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>QA Lead:</strong> 1 person</li>
      <li><strong>QA Engineers:</strong> 2 people</li>
      <li><strong>Automation Engineer:</strong> 1 person</li>
      <li><strong>Tools:</strong> Jira, TestRail, Selenium, Jest, Lighthouse, Axe DevTools</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7. Risk Management</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Risk</th><th>Impact</th><th>Mitigation</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Environment instability</td><td>High</td><td>Daily smoke tests</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Late requirement changes</td><td>Medium</td><td>Change control process</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Resource unavailability</td><td>Medium</td><td>Cross-training team members</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>8. Entry & Exit Criteria</h3>
    <h4>Entry Criteria:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Requirements finalized and approved</li>
      <li>Test environment ready and accessible</li>
      <li>Test cases reviewed and approved</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Exit Criteria:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>100% test case execution</li>
      <li>Zero critical/high severity bugs open</li>
      <li>90%+ pass rate on regression suite</li>
      <li>Sign-off from stakeholders</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- TEST STRATEGY PANEL -->
  <section id="strategy-section" class="doc-section">
    <h2>üéØ Test Strategy</h2>
    
    <h3>1. Overview</h3>
    <p>The Test Strategy defines the high-level approach to testing across all projects. It aligns with business objectives, risk management, and quality goals.</p>

    <h3>2. Testing Principles</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Early Testing:</strong> Shift-left approach; testing begins at requirement phase</li>
      <li><strong>Risk-Based:</strong> Prioritize high-risk, high-impact areas</li>
      <li><strong>Automation-First:</strong> Automate repetitive tests; manual for exploratory</li>
      <li><strong>Continuous Testing:</strong> Integrate testing into CI/CD pipeline</li>
      <li><strong>Defect Prevention:</strong> Focus on preventing defects, not just finding them</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Test Levels & Types</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Level</th><th>Responsibility</th><th>Tools</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Unit Testing</td><td>Developers</td><td>Jest, Mocha, JUnit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Integration Testing</td><td>Developers + QA</td><td>Postman, SuperTest</td></tr>
        <tr><td>System Testing</td><td>QA Engineers</td><td>Selenium, Cypress</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Acceptance Testing</td><td>Product Owners</td><td>Manual, TestRail</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>4. Functional Testing Approach</h3>
    <h4>4.1 Positive Testing</h4>
    <p>Verify expected behavior with valid inputs and typical user workflows.</p>
    
    <h4>4.2 Negative Testing</h4>
    <p>Test system behavior with invalid inputs, edge cases, and error conditions.</p>
    
    <h4>4.3 Boundary Testing</h4>
    <p>Test at limits of input ranges (min, max, just below, just above).</p>

    <h3>5. Non-Functional Testing</h3>
    <h4>5.1 Performance Testing</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Load Testing:</strong> 100-500 concurrent users</li>
      <li><strong>Stress Testing:</strong> Beyond capacity to find breaking point</li>
      <li><strong>Endurance Testing:</strong> 4-8 hour sustained load</li>
      <li><strong>Spike Testing:</strong> Sudden traffic surges</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>5.2 Security Testing</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>OWASP Top 10 vulnerability scanning</li>
      <li>SQL injection, XSS, CSRF testing</li>
      <li>Authentication and authorization checks</li>
      <li>Data encryption verification</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>5.3 Accessibility Testing</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance</li>
      <li>Screen reader compatibility (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)</li>
      <li>Keyboard navigation</li>
      <li>Color contrast ratios</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>5.4 Compatibility Testing</h4>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Category</th><th>Coverage</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Browsers</td><td>Chrome 110+, Firefox 115+, Safari 16+, Edge 110+</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Mobile</td><td>iOS 15+, Android 11+</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Screen Sizes</td><td>320px - 2560px</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>6. Automation Strategy</h3>
    <h4>6.1 Automation Pyramid</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>70% Unit Tests:</strong> Fast, isolated, developer-owned</li>
      <li><strong>20% Integration Tests:</strong> API and service contracts</li>
      <li><strong>10% E2E Tests:</strong> Critical user journeys</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>6.2 Automation Criteria</h4>
    <p>Automate tests that are:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Repetitive and time-consuming</li>
      <li>Part of regression suite</li>
      <li>High-risk critical paths</li>
      <li>Data-driven with multiple permutations</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>6.3 Tools & Frameworks</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Web UI:</strong> Selenium WebDriver, Cypress, Playwright</li>
      <li><strong>API:</strong> Postman, REST Assured, SuperTest</li>
      <li><strong>Mobile:</strong> Appium, Detox</li>
      <li><strong>Performance:</strong> JMeter, k6, Lighthouse CI</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7. Defect Management</h3>
    <h4>7.1 Severity Levels</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Critical:</strong> System crash, data loss, security breach</li>
      <li><strong>High:</strong> Major feature broken, no workaround</li>
      <li><strong>Medium:</strong> Feature partially works, workaround exists</li>
      <li><strong>Low:</strong> Minor UI issue, cosmetic</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>7.2 Priority Levels</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Critical:</strong> Fix immediately, block release</li>
      <li><strong>High:</strong> Fix before release</li>
      <li><strong>Medium:</strong> Fix in next sprint</li>
      <li><strong>Low:</strong> Fix when resources available</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>8. Test Data Management</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Use synthetic data for testing (GDPR compliant)</li>
      <li>Maintain separate test databases per environment</li>
      <li>Automate test data generation and cleanup</li>
      <li>Mask production data if used in lower environments</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>9. Continuous Integration</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Run unit tests on every commit</li>
      <li>Run integration tests on every merge to main</li>
      <li>Run E2E smoke tests on every deployment</li>
      <li>Full regression suite nightly</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>10. Metrics & Reporting</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Target</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Test Coverage</td><td>‚â• 80%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Defect Detection Rate</td><td>‚â• 85%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Test Pass Rate</td><td>‚â• 90%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Automation Coverage</td><td>‚â• 70%</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Mean Time to Detect (MTTD)</td><td>‚â§ 4 hours</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Mean Time to Resolve (MTTR)</td><td>‚â§ 24 hours (Critical)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
